<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMayor.27s_Disability_Council2008">Mayor's Disability Council (May 16, 2008). <a href="http://www.sfgov.org/site/sfmdc_page.asp?id=86619" class="external text" title="http://www.sfgov.org/site/sfmdc_page.asp?id=86619" rel="nofollow">"Resolution in Support of Board of Supervisors’ Ordinance Requiring Activation of Closed Captioning on Televisions in Public Areas"</a>. City and County of San Francisco<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.sfgov.org/site/sfmdc_page.asp?id=86619" class="external free" title="http://www.sfgov.org/site/sfmdc_page.asp?id=86619" rel="nofollow">http://www.sfgov.org/site/sfmdc_page.asp?id=86619</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-01-29</span>.  "that television receivers located in any part of a facility open to the general public have closed captioning activated at all times when the facility is open and the television receiver is in use."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Resolution+in+Support+of+Board+of+Supervisors%E2%80%99+Ordinance+Requiring+Activation+of+Closed+Captioning+on+Televisions+in+Public+Areas&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Mayor%27s+Disability+Council&amp;rft.au=Mayor%27s+Disability+Council&amp;rft.date=May+16%2C+2008&amp;rft.pub=City+and+County+of+San+Francisco&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sfgov.org%2Fsite%2Fsfmdc_page.asp%3Fid%3D86619&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Closed_captioning"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFAlex_Varley.2C_Chief_Executive.2C_Media_Access_Australia2005">Alex Varley, Chief Executive, Media Access Australia (April 18, 2005). <a href="http://www.ada.gov/norwegian.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ada.gov/norwegian.htm" rel="nofollow">"Settlement Agreement Between The United States And Norwegian American Hospital Under The Americans With Disabilities Act"</a>. U.S. Department of Justice<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.ada.gov/norwegian.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.ada.gov/norwegian.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.ada.gov/norwegian.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-01-29</span>.  "...will have closed captioning operating in all public areas where there are televisions with closed captioning; televisions in public areas without built-in closed captioning capability will be replaced with televisions that have such capability"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Settlement+Agreement+Between+The+United+States+And+Norwegian+American+Hospital+Under+The+Americans+With+Disabilities+Act&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Alex+Varley%2C+Chief+Executive%2C+Media+Access+Australia&amp;rft.au=Alex+Varley%2C+Chief+Executive%2C+Media+Access+Australia&amp;rft.date=April+18%2C+2005&amp;rft.pub=U.S.+Department+of+Justice&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ada.gov%2Fnorwegian.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Closed_captioning"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
